lized stylesheet files are located, by&#10;default, in the base theme directory. The name of the locale file will be the&#10;locale followed by '.css'. If that does not exist, then the text direction&#10;stylesheet will be checked for existence, for example 'ltr.css'.&#10;&#10;The theme may change the location of the stylesheet directory by either using&#10;the 'stylesheet_directory_uri' filter or the 'locale_stylesheet_uri' filter.&#10;If you want to change the location of the stylesheet files for the entire&#10;WordPress workflow, then change the former. If you just have the locale in a&#10;separate folder, then change the latter.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@uses apply_filters() Calls 'locale_stylesheet_uri' filter on stylesheet URI path and stylesheet directory URI.&#10;&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="217" lineend="229" name="get_locale_stylesheet_uri" returns="string" signature="string get_locale_stylesheet_uri()"><variable citdl="get_stylesheet_directory()" line="220" name="dir" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="218" name="wp_locale" /><variable citdl="get_locale()" line="221" name="locale" /><variable citdl="get_stylesheet_directory_uri()" line="219" name="stylesheet_dir_uri" /><variable line="222" name="stylesheet_uri" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve name of the current theme.&#10;&#10;@since 1.5.0&#10;@uses apply_filters() Calls 'template' filter on template option.&#10;&#10;@return string Template name." ilk="function" line="239" lineend="241" name="get_template" returns="string" signature="string get_template()" /><scope doc="Retrieve current theme directory.&#10;&#10;@since 1.5.0&#10;@uses apply_filters() Calls 'template_directory' filter on template directory path and template name.&#10;&#10;@return string Template directory path." ilk="function" line="251" lineend="257" name="get_template_directory" returns="string" signature="string get_template_directory()"><variable citdl="string" line="254" name="template_dir" /><variable ci