e of the theme.&#10;	Default is to leverage the main theme root.&#10;@param string $theme_root Optional. The theme root for which calculations will be based, preventing&#10;	the need for a get_raw_theme_root() call.&#10;@return string Themes URI." ilk="function" line="471" lineend="496" name="get_theme_root_uri" returns="string" signature="string get_theme_root_uri(string $stylesheet_or_template = false, string $theme_root = false)"><variable citdl="string" default="false" ilk="argument" line="471" name="stylesheet_or_template" /><variable citdl="string" default="false" ilk="argument" line="471" name="theme_root" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="472" name="wp_theme_directories" /><variable citdl="content_url()" line="480" name="theme_root_uri" /></scope><scope doc="Get the raw theme root relative to the content directory with no filters applied.&#10;&#10;@since 3.1.0&#10;&#10;@param string $stylesheet_or_template The stylesheet or template name of the theme&#10;@param bool $skip_cache Optional. Whether to skip the cache. Defaults to false, meaning the cache is used.&#10;@return string Theme root" ilk="function" line="507" lineend="530" name="get_raw_theme_root" returns="string" signature="string get_raw_theme_root(string $stylesheet_or_template, bool $skip_cache = false)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="507" name="stylesheet_or_template" /><variable citdl="bool" default="false" ilk="argument" line="507" name="skip_cache" /><variable citdl="get_theme_roots()" line="524" name="theme_roots" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="508" name="wp_theme_directories" /><variable citdl="boolean" line="513" name="theme_root" /></scope><scope doc="Display localized stylesheet link element.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0" ilk="function" line="537" lineend="542" name="locale_stylesheet" signature="locale_stylesheet()"><variable citdl="get_locale_stylesheet_uri()" line="538" name="stylesheet" /></scope><scope doc="Start preview theme output buffer.&#10;&#10;Will only perform task if the user has permissions and template and preview&#10;query variables exist.&#10;&#10;@since 2.6.0" ilk="function" line="552" lineend="581" name="preview_theme" signature="preview_theme()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="553" name="_GET" /></scope><scope doc="Private function to modify the current template when previewing a theme&#10;&#10;@since 2.9.0&#10;@access private&#10;&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="592" lineend="594" name="_preview_theme_template_filter" returns="string" signature="string _preview_theme_template_filter()" /><scope doc="Private function to modify the current stylesheet when previewing a theme&#10;&#10;@since 2.9.0&#10;@access private&#10;&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="604" lineend="606" name="_preview_theme_stylesheet_filter" returns="string" signature="string _preview_theme_stylesheet_filter()" /><scope doc="Callback function for ob_start() to capture all links in the theme.&#10;&#10;@since 2.6.0&#10;@access private&#10;&#10;@param string $content&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="617" lineend="619" name="preview_theme_ob_filter" returns="string" signature="string preview_theme_ob_filter(string $content)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="617" name="content" /></scope><scope doc="Manipulates preview theme links in order to control and maintain location.&#10;&#10;Callback function for preg_replace_callback() to accept and filter matches.&#10;&#10;@since 2.6.0&#10;@access private&#10;&#10;@param array $matches&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="632" lineend="650" name="preview_theme_ob_filter_callback" returns="string" signature="string preview_theme_ob_filter_callback(array $matches)"><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="632" name="matches" /><variable citdl="add_query_arg()" line="646" name="link" /></scope><scope doc="Switches the theme.&#10;&#10;Accepts one argument: $stylesheet of the theme. It also accepts an additional function signature&#10;of two arguments: $template then $stylesheet. This is for backwards compatibility.&#10;&#10;@since 2.5.0&#10;@uses do_action() Calls 'switch_theme' action, passing the new theme.&#10;&#10;@param string $stylesheet Stylesheet name" ilk="function" line="663" lineend="701" name="switch_theme" signature="switch_theme(string $stylesheet)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="663" name="stylesheet" /><variable citdl="array()" line="695" name="default_theme_mods" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="664" name="wp_theme_directories" /><variable citdl="new_theme.get()" line="690" name="new_name" /><variable citdl="wp_get_theme()" line="670" name="new_theme" /><variable citdl="stylesheet" line="673" name="template" /><variable citdl="wp_get_theme()" line="669" name="old_theme" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="664" name="sidebars_widgets" /></scope><scope doc="Checks that current theme files 'index.php' and 'style.css' exists.&#10;&#10;Does not check the default theme, which is the fallback and should always exist.&#10;Will switch theme to the fallback theme if current theme does not validate.&#10;You can use the 'validate_current_theme' filter to return false to&#10;disable this functionality.&#10;&#10;@since 1.5.0&#10;@see WP_DEFAULT_THEME&#10;&#10;@return bool" ilk="function" line="716" lineend="737" name="validate_current_theme" returns="bool" signature="bool validate_current_theme()" /><scope doc="Retrieve all theme modifications.&#10;&#10;@since 3.1.0&#10;&#10;@return array Theme modifications." ilk="function" line="746" lineend="759" name="get_theme_mods" returns="array" signature="array get_theme_mods()"><variable citdl="get_option()" line="748" name="mods" /><variable citdl="get_option()" line="749" name="theme_name" /><variable citdl="get_option()" line="747" name="theme_slug" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve theme modification value for the current theme.&#10;&#10;If the modification name does not exist, then the $